hint.text: The total number of students that fall in a particular category is called the frequency.

solution.text:
From the frequency distribution table,
The total number of students falling in the group \((110-120)\) and \((160-170)\) is \(23\).
Therefore, classes \((110-120)\) and \((160-170)\) have the same frequency.
